pos_mean_info_list.mean: 竞争的；比赛的；求胜心切的

word_mean_info__list.difference: 最常用词，通常指在争论、辩论、竞选或竞赛以及其它各种矛盾冲突中站在对立面的“对手”或“敌手”。
指与某人目标一致而想赶上或超过他的人，匹敌者。
语气较强，多用于书面文字和诗歌中。指不仅敌对，而且很危险，怀有很深的敌意。
指为同一目标或目的竞争者，一般无感情色彩。

word_group.brief_definition: 好斗的竞争对手；努力进取的对手
击败竞争对手；打败竞争对手

bilingual.source: They tried to force out their competitor.
bilingual.target: 他们试图封杀竞争对手。
竞争对手的市场份额正在增长。

bilingual.source: The company felt threatened by the new competitor.
bilingual.target: 公司感到受到新竞争对手的威胁。

bilingual.source: He tried to denigrate his competitor's achievements.
bilingual.target: 他试图诋毁他的竞争对手的成就。

bilingual.source: She magnanimously offered to help her competitor.
bilingual.target: 她宽宏大量地提出帮助她的竞争对手。

bilingual.source: The company decided to buy in shares of their competitor.
bilingual.target: 公司决定买入竞争对手的股份。

bilingual.source: The company plans to merge with its competitor next year.
bilingual.target: 公司计划明年与其竞争对手合并。

bilingual.source: The company announced a buyout of its main competitor.
bilingual.target: 公司宣布了对其主要竞争对手的收购。

bilingual.source: The runner overtook his competitor in the final lap.
bilingual.target: 这名跑步者在最后一圈超过了他的竞争对手。

bilingual.source: He was accused of betraying company secrets to a competitor.
bilingual.target: 他被指控背叛公司机密给竞争对手。

yingyinNormal.en: When suddenly, a competitor, if you can call Uncle Sam a competitor, hires my own team, Barney and the whole gang to whack me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 然后，突然一个竞争对手，我把山姆大叔叫做竞争对手,雇了我自己的团队，巴尼和所有队里的人来对付我。

yingyinNormal.en: I will be your competitor. You're up for it. You're a big girl.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我会是你的对手，你得做好准备，你懂的。

yingyinNormal.en: All right, let's say a physician was prescribing one of our competitor's drugs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 假设有个医生，本来开的是我们竞争对手的药。

yingyinNormal.en: Do you know why people buy an Apple? Why do they buy an Apple, not the competitor?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们知道人们为什么买苹果电脑吗？为什么他们买苹果而不是竞争对手的产品？

yingyinNormal.en: He was attempting to sell trade secrets to a competitor. If the suit drags on, it could hang over the stock price.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他试图将公司交易机密卖给竞争对手。如果这个官司拖得太久，可能会影响到股票价格。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Critics say the big companies use such deals to buy their most threatening potential <highlight>competitors</highlight>, as part of a "buy and kill" tactic to simply close them down.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 评论家们说，大公司利用此类交易来收购他们最具威胁性的潜在竞争对手，是“买杀”策略的一部分，此举能够简单地使这些公司倒闭。
淘汰他们潜在的竞争对手。

examination_example.sentence: But it can also be antagonistic such as when a political candidate turns toward their <highlight>competitor</highlight> during a debate and makes eye contact that signals hostility.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但它也可能是敌对性的，例如当一名政治候选人在辩论中转向他们的竞争对手并进行表示敌意的眼神交流。
